#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "API keys versus access tokens"
msgstr "应用程序接口密钥与访问令牌"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Using API keys provides an easiest option for accessing LLM:"
msgstr "使用 API 密钥是访问 LLM 的最简单选择："

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When an AI service serves many users in the organization, the API key must "
"be organization wide for everyone in the organization be able to have their "
"data analyzed by LLM. API key is a long time token which must be kept "
"secured."
msgstr ""
"当人工智能服务为组织中的许多用户提供服务时，API 密钥必须是组织范围内的，这样组织中的每个人才能让 LLM 分析他们的数据。API "
"密钥是一个长期令牌，必须妥善保管。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If your application works with users who log-in with an OpenId Connect "
"provider such as Google, which also hosts LLM, managing API keys with a long "
"lifespan safely is a security challenge that can be avoided given that the "
"time-constrained access tokens acquired during the Google authentication are "
"already available. Furthermore, the organization wide API keys can not be "
"used to access Google services on behalf of the currently logged-in user."
msgstr ""
"如果您的应用程序与使用 OpenId Connect 提供商（如谷歌，它也是 LLM 的主机）登录的用户一起工作，那么安全管理具有较长生命周期的 API "
"密钥就是一个安全挑战，而在谷歌身份验证过程中获得的有时间限制的访问令牌已经可用，因此可以避免这一挑战。此外，组织范围内的 API "
"密钥不能用于代表当前登录用户访问谷歌服务。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As you can see, using access tokens to access Gemini looks similar to using "
"API keys. The difference is, the access token is scoped by the current user "
"authentication, it is time constrained and it can be used to access any "
"Google service that requires an access token."
msgstr ""
"如你所见，使用访问令牌访问 Gemini 看起来与使用 API "
"密钥类似。不同的是，访问令牌的作用域是当前用户身份验证，它有时间限制，可用于访问任何需要访问令牌的谷歌服务。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Using access tokens fits into the integrated security concept perfectly: "
"users login to your application with Google using an OpenId Connect "
"authorization code flow, the application propagates an access token acquired "
"as part of this flow to Google services to access them on behalf of the "
"authenticated user, with the Google Gemini service being only one of such "
"services. The user logs out, the session and the corresponding ID and access "
"tokens are deleted."
msgstr ""
"使用访问令牌完全符合集成安全概念：用户使用 OpenId Connect 授权代码流登录到 Google "
"应用程序，应用程序将在此流程中获取的访问令牌传播到 Google 服务，以代表通过验证的用户访问这些服务，Google Gemini "
"服务只是其中之一。用户注销后，会话以及相应的 ID 和访问令牌将被删除。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And the security bonus point is that the current user will be asked by "
"Google, after the authentication is complete, to authorize your application "
"to use Generative API on the user's behalf."
msgstr "安全方面的额外好处是，在验证完成后，谷歌会要求当前用户授权你的应用程序代表用户使用 Generative API。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Therefore, we will work with the access tokens."
msgstr "因此，我们将使用访问令牌。"

#: _posts/2025-03-13-gemini-personal-assistant.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
